The negative Cash Balance is the accounting balance as on 31st March 2020. This has arisen due to the residual
transactions for Financial Year 2019-2020 accounted for during 1st April, 2020 to 10th April, 2020 by the RBI. As per
the M/o Finance, D/o Economic Affairs letter dated 31.03.2017, RBI had maintained the cash balance limit of
5000.37Crores as on 31.03.2020. However, due to reporting of net payment of  7594.51 Crore as March (Residual)
transactions by the agency banks, the Cash balance as on 31st March, 2020 is negative.
